We are responding to you at the request of the Office of the Governor.



We are sorry to learn of the illness of your mother and hope she will recover quickly so this difficult decision can be avoided. We have received your request for an early retirement and reviewed your circumstances. However, we find that you are not eligible to apply for an early retirement until you attain the age of 60 with an effective retirement date of February 1, 2015.

As a member of the Teachers’ and State Employees’ Retirement System a member becomes eligible for a reduced retirement at age 50 with 20 years of creditable service or at age 60 with 5 years of membership service. However, a member will be eligible for an unreduced retirement at age 60 with 25 years of creditable service, or age 65 with 5 years of membership service, or at any age with at least 30 years of creditable service

According to our records, you currently have 13.7500 years of service, and you are age 54 as of the effective retirement date you have proposed.

You may consider contacting your Human Resources Department to inquire about Family Medical Leave or you may withdraw your contributions from the retirement system upon your termination of employment. Please keep in mind when you withdraw your contributions you also withdraw all rights to any future benefits from this retirement system – your prior service will also be withdrawn. You can purchase your withdrawn service once you have completed 5 years of Membership Service in your current Retirement Account after returning to service.



